      "description": "Offered is a mechanically sorted Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) featuring the iconic 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This example maintains its factory front-midship balance and lightweight aluminum double-wishbone suspension architecture. The drivetrain is robust, with the synchronized 5-speed manual gearbox delivering power through a Torsen limited-slip differential. Recent preventive maintenance includes a full cooling system refresh and inspection of the sequential solenoid control system to ensure seamless boost transition. While the exterior shows honest patina consistent with a well-loved driver, the chassis remains rigid and the 13B housing compression is within healthy operating parameters. A true driver's machine optimized for corner-exit speed and high-revving engagement.",
